			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Senior Software Engineer</strong></p>
<p>
Job Purpose&nbsp;<br />
As a part of the software engineering team, you will participate in the entire software development life-cycle, working with latest java (J2SE/J2EE) technologies to deliver multi-threaded, high performance, scalable applications.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Essential Responsibilities&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Participating in requirements gathering, and reviewing and/or co-authoring technical specification<br />
&bull; Constructing technical designs and implementation as per coding standards<br />
&bull; Defining and carrying out necessary tests i.e. unit, integration, performance, stability<br />
&bull; Performing and participating with peer design and code reviews<br />
&bull; Developing and maintaining necessary documentation i.e. class diagrams, ER diagrams,&nbsp; user manual,&nbsp; programmer manual, test documents, etc.<br />
&bull; Participating in production deployments<br />
&bull; Maintenance and support of live products, and assisting Technical Support<br />
&bull; Providing Level 3 support on a roster basis<br />
&bull; Communicating and liaising with internal and external clients<br />
&bull; Making contribution to improving software development life-cycle and product quality<br />
&bull; Enhancing and contributing to the technical know-how within the team<br />
<br />
Essential Requirements:<br />
&bull; 5+ year experience in Java Software Development &ndash; preferably wireless or Internet industry<br />
&bull; Tertiary qualifications in Computer Science or equivalent discipline<br />
&bull; Good communication and problem-solving skills<br />
&bull; Ability to work reliably as a part of a team<br />
&bull; Strong knowledge of Java, eg: multi-threaded programming, advanced language constructs<br />
&bull; Extensive familiarity with JDK libraries<br />
&bull; Strong experience with SQL databases i.e. MySQL and Oracle<br />
&bull; Experience with JMS<br />
&bull; Experience with Hibernate or equivalent O/R tools&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Experience with software performance and scalability<br />
&bull; Knowledge of software algorithms and agile methodologies<br />
&bull; Familiarity and ability to work with Linux and Windows<br />
&bull; Ability and drive to learn new technologies<br />
&bull; Knowledge and experience with unit testing, test-driven development, and continuous integration&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Desirable<br />
&bull; Telecommunication knowledge i.e. SMS, MMS, WAP-PUSH, SMPP, etc.<br />
&bull; Software profiling and performance tuning knowledge i.e. JProfiler<br />
&bull; SQL scripting desirable<br />
&bull; Experience in application monitoring/management technologies i.e. JMX<br />
&bull; Familiarity with JBoss, managed beans, , etc.<br />
&bull; Familiarity with scripting languages such as PHP, Perl, JRuby, etc.<br />
&bull; Experience with Maven and Mecurial or Git</p>
<p>
<strong>About pavyia</strong><br />
payvia is the most successful mobile direct payments company in America. Directly connected to all major telecommunications carriers in North America, we have just passed the $2 billion mark in processed mobile payments. Our technology investments exceed $70m and our patented IP in transaction processing and smart checkout experiences enable customers to convert users into successful paying customers. payvia dramatically reduces abandoned transactions and increases purchase conversion. payvia takes the complexity out of working with mobile network operators, transforming the operator payment landscape with fast, consistent and reliable settlements</p>
<p>
As part of the MQube (since 1999) group of companies employees with payvia have the opportunity to work in a number of mobile payments, mobile communications, mobile marketing and telecommunications platforms fields, with both local and global opportunities for growth.</p>
<p>
We offer competitive pay and benefits, challenging work and rewards for performance.</p>
